{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Kerala", "text_new": "{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Kerala, India}}\n{{Current event|2=current disease pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] in [[Kerala|Kerala, India]]\n| width           =\n| map1            = {{wdib|ps=1|P1846|sep=\"--\"|df=dmy}}\n| legend1         = Map of districts with confirmed cases\n{{legend|#d45500ff|30+ confirmed cases}}\n{{legend|#ff9955ff|10\u201329 confirmed cases}}\n{{legend|#ffe6d5ff|1\u20139 confirmed cases}}\n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Kerala]], [[India]]\n| first_case      = [[Thrissur]]\n| arrival_date    = 30 January 2020<br>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=01|day1=30|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          =\n<!-- The confirmed, active, recovery and deaths cases are fetched from the Wikidata; Kindly don't delete the codes below.-->\n| confirmed_cases = {{stringsplit | txt={{wdib|ps=1|P1603|qual=P585|sep=\"--\"|df=dmy}} |sep=\"--\" |idx=-1}}<ref name=\"GoKDB\">{{cite web |title=Kerala : Covid-19 Battle |url=https://dashboard.kerala.gov.in/index.php |access-date=3 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200407151754/https://dashboard.kerala.gov.in/index.php |archive-date=7 April 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| active_cases    = {{#expr: {{stringsplit | txt={{wdib|ps=1|P1603|sep=\"--\"|df=dmy}} |sep=\"--\" |idx=-1}}-{{stringsplit | txt={{wdib|ps=1|P8010|sep=\"--\"|df=dmy}} |sep=\"--\" |idx=-1}}-{{stringsplit | txt={{wdib|ps=1|P1120|sep=\"--\"|df=dmy}} |sep=\"--\" |idx=-1}}}} <ref name=\"GoKDB\"/>\n| recovery_cases  = {{stringsplit | txt={{wdib|ps=1|P8010|qual=P585|sep=\"--\"|df=dmy}} |sep=\"--\" |idx=-1}}<ref name=\"GoKDB\"/>\n| deaths          = {{stringsplit | txt={{wdib|ps=1|P1120|qual=P585|sep=\"--\"|df=dmy}} |sep=\"--\" |idx=-1}}<ref name=\"GoKDB\"/>\n| territories     = Entire state\n| total_ili       =\n| website         = {{url|http://dhs.kerala.gov.in}}\n}}\nThe [[2019-2020 coronavirus pandemic]] was first confirmed in India on 30 January 2020, in the state of [[Kerala]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Narasimhan |first1=T. E. |title=India's first coronavirus case: Kerala student in Wuhan tested positive |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/current-affairs/india-s-first-coronavirus-case-kerala-student-in-wuhan-tested-positive-120013001782_1.html |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=Business Standard India |agency=Business Standard |date=30 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311040438/https://www.business-standard.com/article/current-affairs/india-s-first-coronavirus-case-kerala-student-in-wuhan-tested-positive-120013001782_1.html |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name = weather>{{cite news |title=Kerala Defeats Coronavirus; India's Three COVID-19 Patients Successfully Recover |url=https://weather.com/en-IN/india/news/news/2020-02-14-kerala-defeats-coronavirus-indias-three-covid-19-patients-successfully |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=The Weather Channel |agency=Weather Channel |publisher=TWC India Edit Team |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200218172552/https://weather.com/en-IN/india/news/news/2020-02-14-kerala-defeats-coronavirus-indias-three-covid-19-patients-successfully |archive-date=18 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> As of 11 April 2020, there have been 374 confirmed cases with 143 recoveries and 2 deaths in the state.<ref name=\"GoKDB\"/>\n\n==Governmental actions==\n[[File:Healthcare workers wearing PPE 03.jpg|thumb|Healthcare workers wearing personal protective equipment for caregiving for a patient with coronavirus infection in a government hospital in Kerala.]]\nThe government of Kerala declared high alert from 4 to 8 February and starting 8 March 2020 due to coronavirus cases being reported from the state.<ref name = ecfeb8/><ref name = gulfnews/>  Isolation wards with 40 beds were set up in 21 major hospitals of the state and a helpline was activated in every district.<ref>{{cite news |first1=Jeemon |last1=Jacob |first2=Sonali |last2=Acharjee |title=How Kerala tamed the Coronavirus |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/magazine/up-front/story/20200224-how-kerala-tamed-the-coronavirus-1646259-2020-02-14 |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=India Today |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308175907/https://www.indiatoday.in/magazine/up-front/story/20200224-how-kerala-tamed-the-coronavirus-1646259-2020-02-14 |archive-date=8 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> As of 9 March, more than 4000 persons are under home or hospital quarantine in Kerala.<ref name=\"ectimes\">{{cite news |title=3-yr-old from Kerala becomes first child in India to test positive for coronavirus |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/three-year-old-from-kerala-becomes-indias-40th-coronavirus-case/articleshow/74545428.cms |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=The Economic Times |date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311040605/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/three-year-old-from-kerala-becomes-indias-40th-coronavirus-case/articleshow/74545428.cms |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> As of 4 March, 215 health care workers were deployed across Kerala and 3,646 tele counselling services were conducted to provide psycho-social support to families of those suspected to be infected.<ref name =theweek>{{cite web |title=Kerala's robust health system shows the way to tackle coronavirus |url=https://www.theweek.in/news/india/2020/03/04/keralas-robust-health-system-shows-the-way-to-tackle-coronavirus.html |website=The Week |accessdate=9 March 2020 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311040631/https://www.theweek.in/news/india/2020/03/04/keralas-robust-health-system-shows-the-way-to-tackle-coronavirus.html |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Despite the threat of coronavirus infection, the Kerala government decided to go ahead with ''[[Attukal pongala]]'', a large, annual, all-women religious congregation in [[Thiruvananthapuram]]. The government also urged individuals to refrain themselves from the ''pongala'', take precautions against disease transmission and, if possible, offer ''pongala'' at their own homes.<ref name = indiatodaymar9 /><ref>{{cite news |title=As coronavirus cases surge, Kerala put on high alert |url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/as-coronavirus-cases-surge-kerala-put-on-high-alert-11583736369396.html |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=Livemint |date=9 March 2020 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311041345/https://www.livemint.com/news/india/as-coronavirus-cases-surge-kerala-put-on-high-alert-11583736369396.html |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The government of Kerala has started a YouTube channel for updating the public regarding the status of coronavirus spread in Kerala and precautions to be taken.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kerala Health Online Training |url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCSE0zP8darFGvDn3CyC2ERg |website=YouTube |accessdate=9 March 2020 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311041411/https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCSE0zP8darFGvDn3CyC2ERg |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> There are three coronavirus testing centres in Kerala : National Institute of Virology Field Unit, [[Thiruvananthapuram Medical College]], [[Calicut Medical College]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus test in India: Complete list of testing sites for coronavirus in India {{!}} India News - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/52-testing-sites-for-coronavirus-in-india/articleshow/74547684.cms |accessdate=12 March 2020 |work=The Times of India |agency=The Times of India |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311180233/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/52-testing-sites-for-coronavirus-in-india/articleshow/74547684.cms |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 10 March, the Kerala government arranged special isolation wards in prisons across the state.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kerala jails to set up isolation cells for suspected coronavirus-infected inmates |url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/kerala-jails-to-set-up-isolation-cells-for-suspected-coronavirus-infected-inmates20200310102829/ |accessdate=10 March 2020 |work=ANI News |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311041429/https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/kerala-jails-to-set-up-isolation-cells-for-suspected-coronavirus-infected-inmates20200310102829/ |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 10 March, the government of Kerala shut down all colleges and schools up to grade 7.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Six fresh cases reported in Kerala; Schools, colleges, cinemas shut till March 31 |url=https://www.financialexpress.com/lifestyle/health/coronavirus-six-fresh-cases-reported-in-kerala-schools-colleges-cinemas-shut-till-march-31/1894165/ |website=The Financial Express |accessdate=11 March 2020 |date=10 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311153430/https://www.financialexpress.com/lifestyle/health/coronavirus-six-fresh-cases-reported-in-kerala-schools-colleges-cinemas-shut-till-march-31/1894165/ |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The government also urged people to not undertake pilgrimages, attend large gatherings such as weddings and cinema shows.<ref name = mar10/>\n\nAlso, the government has launched a mobile application called GoK Direct for users to get information and updates regarding the COVID-19 (coronavirus) disease. It is an initiative from the Kerala Startup Mission and the Information & Public Relations Department. The app can also send text message alerts to basic phones (without internet).<ref>{{cite news |title=Kerala govt launches mobile app for users to track coronavirus updates |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/kerala-govt-launches-mobile-app-users-track-coronavirus-updates-120104/ |accessdate=13 March 2020 |work=The News Minute News |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315062035/https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/kerala-govt-launches-mobile-app-users-track-coronavirus-updates-120104 |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, a new initiative 'Break the Chain' was introduced by Government of Kerala.The campaign aims to educate people about the importance of public and personal hygiene.\nUnder this campaign, the [[Pinarayi Vijayan]]-led government has installed water taps at public spots such as at the entry and exit gates of the railway stations with hand wash bottles.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kerala govt launches break the chain initiative for personal hygiene |url=https://www.ndtv.com/kerala-news/kerala-launches-break-the-chain-campaign-to-combat-coronavirus-2196103%3famp=1&akamai-rum=off|accessdate=15 March 2020 |work=NDTV |language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 March, Chief minister [[Pinarayi Vijayan]] announced a stimulus package of Rs 20,000 crore ([[Euro|\u20ac2.5 billion]]; [[US Dollar|$2.6 billion]]) to help the state overcome both the covid-19 epidemic and economic hardship caused by it. This includes Rs. 500 crore for healthcare, Rs 2,000 crore for loans and free rations,  Rs 2,000 crore for creating jobs in rural areas, Rs 1,000 crore for families with financial difficulties, and Rs 1,320 crore for paying two months pensions in advance.<ref name = \"Stimulus\">{{cite news | last = Sneha Mary Koshy | title = 1 More Tests Positive For Coronavirus, Kerala Announces Rs 20,000 Crore Package | newspaper = NDTV | location =  | pages =  | language = English | date = 20 March 2020 | url = https://www.ndtv.com/kerala-news/coronavirus-1-more-tests-positive-kerala-announces-rs-20-000-crore-package-2197698 | access-date = 25 March 2020 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200325031308/https://www.ndtv.com/kerala-news/coronavirus-1-more-tests-positive-kerala-announces-rs-20-000-crore-package-2197698 | archive-date = 25 March 2020 | url-status = live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last =  | title = Kerala government announces Rs 20,000 crore package to tackle coronavirus outbreak | newspaper = Hindustan Times | location =  | pages =  | language = English | date = 20 March 2020 | url = https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/kerala-government-announces-rs-20-000-crore-package-to-tackle-coronavirus-outbreak/story-KzGvehTH4HXjhnkTBLU49M.html | access-date = 25 March 2020 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200324192658/https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/kerala-government-announces-rs-20-000-crore-package-to-tackle-coronavirus-outbreak/story-KzGvehTH4HXjhnkTBLU49M.html | archive-date = 24 March 2020 | url-status = live }}</ref> The government has also ordered salons and workout centres to shut down. This is in order to prevent the virus from spreading via direct contact.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.manoramaonline.com/health/health-news/2020/03/09/covid-19-local-transmission.html |title=\u0d15\u0d4b\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d21\u0d4d\u2013 19; \u0d15\u0d3e\u0d30\u0d4d\u0d2f\u0d19\u0d4d\u0d19\u0d7e \u0d15\u0d41\u0d31\u0d1a\u0d4d\u0d1a\u0d41 \u0d38\u0d19\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d40\u0d7c\u0d23\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d23\u0d4d, \u0d17\u0d57\u0d30\u0d35\u0d24\u0d30\u0d35\u0d41\u0d02 |access-date=2020-03-19 |language=ml |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321164929/https://www.manoramaonline.com/health/health-news/2020/03/09/covid-19-local-transmission.html |archive-date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, Health mister of Kerala, [[K. K. Shailaja]] strongly warned to people to follow the orders from Health department of [[Kerala]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://english.mathrubhumi.com/news/kerala/people-must-follow-directions-of-govt-k-k-shailaja-1.4635662|title=People must follow directions of Govt: K K Shailaja|website=Mathrubhumi|accessdate=26 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322085000/https://english.mathrubhumi.com/news/kerala/people-must-follow-directions-of-govt-k-k-shailaja-1.4635662|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, Chief minister [[Pinarayi Vijayan]] announced a statewide lockdown till 31st of march to prevent further spread of [[Coronavirus]].Being strictly applied in [[Kasargod]] necessary shops like grocery stores were allowed to be opened till 11am till 5pm. And in other districts necessary shops were opened from 7 am till 5 pm with the exception of medical stores. Public transports were shut down. There was no restriction for private vehicles but district to district travels were only allowed with thorough checking.<ref name = \"Shutdown\">{{cite web|url=https://www.asianetnews.com/kerala-news/covid-19-pinarayi-vijyan-announce-lock-down-in-kerala-q7ncg5|title=\u0d15\u0d47\u0d30\u0d33\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d3f\u0d7d \u0d32\u0d4b\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d4d \u0d21\u0d57\u0d7a; \u0d38\u0d02\u0d38\u0d4d\u0d25\u0d3e\u0d28\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d4d \u0d07\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d4d 28 \u0d2a\u0d47\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d4d \u0d15\u0d4a\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d21\u0d4d, \u0d15\u0d3e\u0d38\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d15\u0d4b\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d4d \u0d38\u0d4d\u0d25\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d3f \u0d05\u0d24\u0d40\u0d35 \u0d17\u0d41\u0d30\u0d41\u0d24\u0d30\u0d02|website=Asianet News Network Pvt Ltd|accessdate=26 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323133353/https://www.asianetnews.com/kerala-news/covid-19-pinarayi-vijyan-announce-lock-down-in-kerala-q7ncg5|archive-date=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Quarantine==\nKerala is the only state in India that mandates 28 days of home quarantine for those returning from countries affected by coronavirus, while the national guidelines for India is 14 days.<ref name =theweek/><ref>{{cite news |title=How Travelers Around the World Are Dealing With 'Voluntary' Home Quarantines Over Coronavirus Fears |url=https://time.com/5785258/china-coronavirus-home-quarantine/ |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=Time |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224235723/https://time.com/5785258/china-coronavirus-home-quarantine/ |archive-date=24 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> People who are advised home quarantine are advised to stay at their homes during the 28-day period, and report to healthcare authorities if they show symptoms of coronavirus infection.<ref>{{cite news |title=Another Wuhan University Student from Kerala Tested Positive with Novel Coronavirus |url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/another-wuhan-university-student-from-kerala-tested-positive-with-novel-coronavirus-2484719.html |work=News18 |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311041512/https://www.news18.com/news/india/another-wuhan-university-student-from-kerala-tested-positive-with-novel-coronavirus-2484719.html |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Sample Tesing==\nTill date, {{stringsplit | txt={{wdib|ps=1|P8011|sep=\"--\"|df=dmy}} |sep=\"--\" |idx=-1}} samples of suspect cases have been sent for testing.<ref name=\"GoKDB\"/>\n\n== Statistics ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/India/Kerala medical cases chart}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/India/Kerala medical cases}}\n\n<!--|col1='''Case no''':\n{{legend|#bbffbb|Recovered (no detectable virus)}}\n{{legend|#FFFCBB|Clinically recovered}}\n{{legend|#D3D3D3|Not reported}}-->\n{{Columns\n|col1='''Type of Transmission''':\n* {{legend|#bbffbb|'''T''' \u2013 Travel-related}}\n* {{legend|#ffff96|'''T/PTP''' \u2013 Travel related person-to-person spread, usually family and close contacts}}\n* {{legend|#f5deb3|'''PTP''' \u2013 Person-to-person local or community spread (or of unclear origin)}}\n|col1width=55em\n|}}