eb.archive.org/web/20200311040703/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/coronavirus-over-3000-people-still-under-observation-says-govt/articleshow/74034608.cms |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> They belonged to [[Thrissur district|Thrissur]], [[Alappuzha district|Alappuzha]] and [[Kasaragod district|Kasargod]] districts of Kerala and two of them were medical students at a University in Wuhan.<ref name = ecfeb8>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: Over 3000 people still under observation, says govt |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/coronavirus-over-3000-people-still-under-observation-says-govt/articleshow/74034608.cms |work=The Economic Times |date=8 February 2020 |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311040703/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/coronavirus-over-3000-people-still-under-observation-says-govt/articleshow/74034608.cms |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus outbreak: Third virus case reported from Kerala, student who returned from Wuhan tests positive |url=https://www.financialexpress.com/india-news/coronavirus-outbreak-third-virus-case-reported-from-kerala-student-who-returned-from-wuhan-tests-positive/1855081/ |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=The Financial Express |date=4 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311040741/https://www.financialexpress.com/india-news/coronavirus-outbreak-third-virus-case-reported-from-kerala-student-who-returned-from-wuhan-tests-positive/1855081/ |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Following the detection of positive cases, the government of Kerala declared a 'state calamity warning'. Over 3000 contacts of the affected individuals were placed under quarantine, out of which 45 were placed in hospital quarantine.<ref name = ecfeb8/> The three positive individuals later recovered from the infection following hospital care.<ref name=\"quartz\">{{cite news |last1=Kurian |first1=Oommen C. |title=How an Indian state successfully fought and contained the deadly coronavirus |url=https://qz.com/india/1802684/indias-kerala-defeated-deadly-coronavirus-using-information/ |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=Quartz India |agency=Quartz |publisher=Quartz India |date=14 February 2020 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301172622/https://qz.com/india/1802684/indias-kerala-defeated-deadly-coronavirus-using-information/ |archive-date=1 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The 'state calamity' warning was withdrawn after 4 days, when no further cases were reported. As China was a popular country for students from Kerala to pursue medicine, several medical students got stranded in China when the lock-down due to coronavirus was put into effect. Some of them, who were stranded in airports in China were evacuated and flown into [[Cochin International Airport]] and quarantined at isolation wards in [[Kochi Medical College]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: 15 students stranded in China brought to Kochi |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/coronavirus-15-students-stranded-in-china-brought-to-kochi/article30766469.ece |work=The Hindu |date=8 February 2020 |language=en-IN |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305190852/https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/coronavirus-15-students-stranded-in-china-brought-to-kochi/article30766469.ece |archive-date=5 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> However, none of them were later tested positive for the disease.\n! style=\"width: 12%;\"| Total Cases (3)<br>Recovered (3)<br>Death (0)\n|-\n! rowspan=\"20\" style=\"width: 6%;\" | '''March'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''8 March''' ||\n* '''5 Cases''' : The positive cases were a couple and their 26-year-old son, who had returned to Kerala from Italy.<ref name= italyfamily>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus Cases In India Rise To 39, Centre Bans 