 was undergoing treatment at a private hospital over the last two weeks.<ref>{{cite news|title=71-year-old Mahe native dies in Pariyaram Medical College, 3rd COVID-19 death in Kerala|url=https://english.manoramaonline.com/news/kerala/2020/04/11/kerala-third-coronavirus-death-kannur-pariyaram-mahe.html|date=31 March 2020|work=manoramaonline.com|language=en|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> After his condition worsened, he was tested for COVID-19 and was found positive. He was suffering from kidney and heart ailments and was put on ventilator support. The health workers are yet to trace the source of his infection. He was not found to have traveled abroad recently. Preliminary investigation revealed that he had attended several events before being admitted to the hospital on March 27.<ref>{{cite news|title=68-year-old man dies of coronavirus in Kerala, second death in state: Govt|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/south/kerala-reports-third-covid-19-death-as-71-year-old-man-dies-823996.html|date=31 March 2020|work=deccanherald.com|language=en|access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=8| {{note|1|Note 1}}: <small>[[Mahe]] is in the Union Territory of [[Puducherry]], though it is geographically located in [[Kerala]].</small>\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%\"\n|+ style=\"font-size:11pt;\" |{{nowrap|Details for Keralites COVID-19 cases who died outside Kerala (As of 11 April 2020)}}\n! Case order\n! Age\n! Gender\n! style=\"width:100px;\"| Native\n! style=\"width:190px;\"| Country (Death)\n! style=\"width:100px;\"| Status\n! Note\n|-\n| 1\n| 57\n| Male\n| [[Kottayam]]\n| {{flagdeco|Italy}} [[Milan]], [[Italy]]\n| {{failure|Died on 19 March}}\n| The patient hailing from Kadamanchira near [[Changanassery]] was working as a nurse in [[Milan]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Malayali nurse in Italy dies of suspected Covid-19 infection|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/kerala/2020/mar/19/malayali-nurse-in-italy-dies-of-suspected-covid-19-infe