k City|New York]], [[United States]]\n| {{failure|Died on 8 April}}\n| The patient died in the [[Rockland County]].\n|-\n| 25\n| 64\n| Male\n| [[Pathanamthitta]]\n| {{flagdeco|United States}} [[Philadelphia]], [[United States]]\n| {{failure|Died on 8 April}}\n| The patient hailing from [[Kozhencherry]] was working as a traffic controller in the country.<ref>{{cite news|title=Malayali deaths abroad rises to 24|url=https://english.manoramaonline.com/news/kerala/2020/04/08/coronavirus-keralites-death-abroad.html|date=8 April 2020|work=manoramaonline.com|language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n| 26\n| 78\n| Male\n| [[Kottayam]]\n| {{flagdeco|United States}} [[New York City|New York]], [[United States]]\n| {{failure|Died on 9 April}}\n| The patient native of [[Ponkunnam]] was a former workman at [[New York Public Library]] and a resident of [[Rockland County, New York]].<ref>{{cite news|title=A native of Ponkunnam, Kottayam, died of COVID 19 in the United States|url=https://www.mangalam.com/news/detail/387422-latest-news-covid-19one-more-malayalee-died-in-us.html|date=9 April 2020|work=mangalam.com|language=Malayalam}}</ref>\n|-\n| 27\n| 85\n| Male\n| [[Pathanamthitta]]\n| {{flagdeco|United States}} [[New York City|New York]], [[United States]]\n| {{failure|Died on 9 April}}\n| The patient was a native of [[Naranganam]].<ref>{{cite news|title=2 more Malayalees die in US|url=https://www.manoramaonline.com/news/kerala/2020/04/10/corona-virus-two-more-malayali-dies-in-us.html|date=9 April 2020|work=manoramaonline.com|language=Malayalam}}</ref>\n|-\n| 28\n| 49\n| Male\n| [[Ernakulam]]\n| {{flagdeco|United Kingdom}} [[Derbyshire]], [[United Kingdom]]\n| {{failure|Died on 10 April}}\n| The patient hailing from [[Koothattukulam]] was an employee at Old age home in [[Derby]].<ref>{{cite news|title=One more Malayalee dies in Britain|url=https://malayalam.news18.com/news/kerala/one-more-malayalee-dies-in-britain-due-to-covid-19-jj-226445.html|date=10 April 2020|work=malayalam.news18.com|language=Malayalam}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Misinformation and conspiracy theories regarding coronavirus==\n{{main|Misinformation related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus outbreak}}\nFollowing the reports of coronavirus infection in Kerala, fake news regarding prevention, transmission and cure for coronavirus infection started circulating on the internet, particularly on the social media platform Whatsapp.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.manoramaonline.com/health/health-news/2020/03/19/corona-virus-transmission-mental-health-support.html |title=Jostin Francis '\u0d15\u0d4a\u0d31\u0d4b\u0d23 \u0d2d\u0d40\u0d24\u0d3f' \u0d28\u0d3f\u0d19\u0d4d\u0d19\u0d33\u0d46 \u0d35\u0d40\u0d7c\u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d2a\u0d41\u0d2e\u0d41\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d3f\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d41\u0d23\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d4b? \u0d07\u0d24\u0d3e \u0d1a\u0d3f\u0d32 \u0d2a\u0d30\u0d3f\u0d39\u0d3e\u0d30\u0d19\u0d4d\u0d19\u0d33\u0d4d\u200d |access-date=2020-03-19 |language=ml |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319175817/https://www.manoramaonline.com/health/health-news/2020/03/19/corona-virus-transmission-mental-health-support.html |archive-date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name= aljazeerafakenews >{{cite news |title=Misinformation, fake news spark India coronavirus fears |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/misinformation-fake-news-spark-india-coronavirus-fears-200309051731540.html |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=aljazeera.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309153106/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/misinformation-fake-news-spark-india-coronavirus-fears-200309051731540.html |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOne fake message claiming to be an advisory from UNICEF asks people to avoid ice creams to ensure that coronavirus cannot spread in temperatures over 27 degrees.<ref name=\"aljazeerafakenews\" />\n\n[[T. P. Senkumar]] posted on social media that virus cannot survive in the hot and humid conditions in Kerala because the temperature there is over 27 degrees.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Madhu |first1=Aami |title=\u0d15\u0d4a\u0d31\u0d4b\u0d23 \u0d15\u0d47\u0d30\u0d33\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d46 \u0d1a\u0d42\u0d1f\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d4d\u200d \u0d35\u0d30\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d4d\u0d32\u0d46\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d4d \u0d38\u0d46\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d\u0d15\u0d41\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d; \u0d2a\u0d4a\u0d33\u0d3f\u0d1a\u0d4d\u0d1a\u0d1f\u0d41\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d3f \u0d21\u0d4b\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d31\u0d41\u0d1f\u0d46 \u0d15\u0d41\u0d31\u0d3f\u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d2a\u0d4d |url=https://malayalam.oneindia.com/news/kerala/tp-senkumar-about-corona-virus-243241.html |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=malayalam.oneindia.com |date=6 March 2020 |language=ml |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307215402/https://malayalam.oneindia.com/news/kerala/tp-senkumar-about-corona-virus-243241.html |archive-date=7 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Another fake news recommends intake of vitamin C and drinking frequent sips of water as a preventive measure for coronavirus infection.<ref name=\"aljazeerafakenews\" />\n\nAnother post on Facebook claimed falsely that if someone takes a deep breath and holds their breath for more than 10 seconds without coughing, without discomfort, stiffness or tightness, etc., it proves there is no (COVID-19 caused) fibrosis in the lungs, therefore indicating no infection.<ref name= 10secondsrule >{{cite news |title=Fact check: Will holding your breath for 10 seconds reveal if you have coronavirus? |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/factcheck/2020/03/22/coronavirus-fact-check-your-holding-breath-test-covid-19/2891572001/ |accessdate=23 March 2020 |website=USA Today |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323051122/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/factcheck/2020/03/22/coronavirus-fact-check-your-holding-breath-test-covid-19/2891572001/ |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe claim that the vibration generated by clapping together during Janata curfew will kill the virus was debunked by the media.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mohanlal, many others share fake info that 'clapping may kill virus', PIB debunks |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/mohanlal-many-others-share-fake-info-clapping-may-kill-virus-pib-debunks-120844 |accessdate=23 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330170223/https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/mohanlal-many-others-share-fake-info-clapping-may-kill-virus-pib-debunks-120844 |archive-date=30 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> One viral message says that the lifetime of coronavirus is only 12 hours and staying home for 14 hours during Janata curfew break the chain of transmission. Another message claimed that observing Janata curfew will result in the reduction of coronavirus cases by 40%.<ref>{{cite news |title=Fact Check: Social media users give misleading twist to PM Modi's concept of 'Janta curfew' |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/fact-check/story/social-media-users-give-misleading-twist-pm-modi-janta-curfew-1658195-2020-03-21 |accessdate=23 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330170224/https://www.indiatoday.in/fact-check/story/social-media-users-give-misleading-twist-pm-modi-janta-curfew-1658195-2020-03-21 |archive-date=30 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Economic loss==\nTourism industry is a major contributor to the state's economy. Following coronavirus confirmation in Kerala, there were waves of cancellations of hotel bookings and tour packages.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/coronavirus-live-update-two-chinese-nationals-quarantined-in-hyderabad-11580994153313.html|title=Coronavirus India live update: All 645 evacuees from Wuhan test negative|date=6 February 2020|work=Livemint|accessdate=9 March 2020|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314183513/https://www.livemint.com/news/india/coronavirus-live-update-two-chinese-nationals-quarantined-in-hyderabad-11580994153313.html|archive-date=14 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>  Liquor sales in Kerala is a public sector undertaking, through which the government earns a significant revenue. However, following the outbreak, the sales have gone down, directly hitting the economy. The state's economy is largely dependent on [[Non-resident Indian and person of Indian origin|NRI]] remittances and the economic slowdown of affected Gulf countries is expected to have a direct impact.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://english.manoramaonline.com/business/news/2020/03/11/covid-19-will-impact-kerala-economy-says-thomas-isaac.html|title=COVID-19 will impact Kerala economy, says Thomas Isaac|website=OnManorama|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319005208/https://english.manoramaonline.com/business/news/2020/03/11/covid-19-will-impact-kerala-economy-says-thomas-isaac.html|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Kerala State Road Transport Corporation|KSRTC]], Kerala's state-owned public transport system has reported losses worth crores due to reduced number of travelers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/steps-to-cushion-economic-fallout-of-covid-19/article31085818.ece|title=Kerala initiates steps to cushion economic fallout of COVID-19|date=2020-03-17|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-03-19|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319005208/https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/steps-to-cushion-economic-fallout-of-covid-19/article31085818.ece|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The practice of social distancing has also brought down the numbers of those who go out on weekends or do shopping, thus affecting local traders and vendors.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.freepressjournal.in/india/from-empty-beaches-to-cancelled-bus-services-how-coronavirus-has-impacted-keralas-economy|title=From empty beaches to cancelled bus services, how coronavirus has impacted Kerala's economy|website=Free Press Journal|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319005217/https://www.freepressjournal.in/india/from-empty-beaches-to-cancelled-bus-services-how-coronavirus-has-impacted-keralas-economy|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in India]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in India}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in India by state or union territory|Kerala]]\n[[Category:Health in Kerala]]\n[[Category:2020s in Kerala]]\n[[Category:Disasters in Kerala]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eTimeline of events:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: Comfirmed \u2192 Confirmed", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Kerala"}
