s], University of Bergen. Retrieved 16 September 2010.\n:* [http://www.wittgensteinsource.org/ Wittgenstein Source], University of Bergen. Retrieved 16 September 2010.\n* [http://www.wittgen-cam.ac.uk/ The Cambridge Wittgenstein Archive]. Retrieved 16 September 2010.\n\n===Papers about his ''Nachlass''===\n* {{cite journal|first1=David|last1=Stern|title=The Bergen Electronic Edition of Wittgenstein's Nachlass|journal=European Journal of Philosophy|date=2010-09-01|issn=1468-0378|pages=455\u2013467|volume=18|issue=3|doi=10.1111/j.1468-0378.2010.00425.x|url=https://zenodo.org/record/1038591}}\n* Von Wright, G.H. [https://www.jstor.org/pss/2184200 \"The Wittgenstein Papers\"], ''The Philosophical Review''. 78, 1969.\n\n===Other===\n\n* [[Gordon Park Baker|Baker, G.P.]] and [[Peter Hacker|Hacker, P. M. S.]] ''Wittgenstein: Understanding and Meaning''. Blackwell, 1980.\n* Baker, G.P. and Hacker, P. M. S. ''Wittgenstein: Rules, Grammar, and Necessity''. Blackwell, 1985.\n* Baker, G.P. and Hacker, P. M. S. ''Wittgenstein: Meaning and Mind''. Blackwell, 1990.\n* Baker, Gordon P., and Katherine J. Morris. ''Wittgenstein's Method: Neglected Aspects: Essays on Wittgenstein.'' Malden, MA: Blackwell Pub., 2004.\n* Brockhaus, Richard R. ''Pulling Up the Ladder: The Metaphysical Roots of Wittgenstein's Tractatus Logico-Philosophicus''. Open Court, 1990.\n* [[James F. Conant|Conant, James F.]] \"Putting Two and Two Together: Kierkegaard, Wittgenstein and the Point of View for Their Work as Authors\" in ''The Grammar of Religious Belief'', edited by [[D.Z. Phillips]]. St. Martins Press, NY: 1996\n* [[Alice Crary|Crary, Alice]]. \"Wittgenstein goes to Frankfurt (and finds something useful to say).\" ''Nordic Wittgenstein Review'' vol. 7, no. 1 (June 2018): 7-41.\n* Engelmann, Paul. Letters from Ludwig Wittgenstein. Basil Blackwell, 1967\n* {{cite news |last=Fraser |first=Giles |url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/belief/2010/jan/25/wittgenstein-philosophical-investigations |